  "translations": {
    "en": "deputies. Surely, the Imamate is the vicegerency of Allah, Mighty and Majestic, the vicegerency of the Messenger (peace be upon him and his family), the rank of the Commander of the Faithful (peace be upon him), and the inheritance of al-Hasan and al-Husayn (peace be upon them both). Surely, the Imamate is the reins of the religion, the order of the Muslims, the rectification of this world, and the glory of the believers. Surely, the Imamate is the growing foundation of Islam and its lofty branch. Through the Imam, prayer, alms, fasting, Hajj, jihad, the apportionment of spoils of war and charity, the implementation of limits and rulings, and the protection of frontiers and borders are perfected. The Imam makes permissible what Allah makes permissible, makes forbidden what Allah makes forbidden, establishes the limits of Allah, defends the religion of Allah, and calls to the way of his Lord with wisdom, goodly exhortation, and clear proof.",
